                <div>
                    <h2>Who are we?</h2>
                    <p>The Oaks Childcare Clubs CIC is a not for profit organisation (a community interest company) providing a fun, safe place for children 
                        of different ages to play, relax and spend time before and after the school day.</p>
                    <p>The Oaks Club was started over 15 years ago and has evolved from one club run by volunteer parents to a community interest company 
                        running 6 clubs in 3 locations with over 250 children being looked after by a friend, professional and caring team of around 30 staff.</p>
                    <p><a href="/clubs">Our Clubs</a> are based in Burghfield and Mortimer.  Do <a href="/contact">get in touch</a> if you are looking for
                        wrap around care at your school, or if you are interested in <a href="/join">working for us</a></p>
                    <p>If your child has a place at <a href="https://burghfield.w-berks.sch.uk" target="_blank">Burghfield St Mary’s Primary School</a>, 
                        <a href="https://www.msj.w-berks.sch.uk" target="_blank">Mortimer St John’s Infant School</a> or <a href="https://msm.w-berks.sch.uk" target="_blank">Mortimer St Mary’s Primary School</a>, you can 
                        register for a place and/or contact us for more information.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
